# Env vars for shells spawned in canvas xterm/tmux sessions. The ensembleworks-term
# gateway drops these shells to the ensembleworks-agent sandbox user; this file is
# sourced into every interactive shell by ~/.bashrc under `set -a`, so anything
# launched from a canvas terminal (opencode, ad-hoc curl, …) sees these vars.
#
# Plain KEY=value — no `export`. Edit then open a NEW terminal (or `source
# ~/.bashrc`) to apply. Keep chmod 600. deploy.sh seeds this placeholder once and
# never overwrites it, so the filled-in key survives redeploys. Off-repo on the box.
OPENCODE_API_KEY=
